SU2 Headquarters<br>
<br>
Kate walked into the building carrying two cups of coffee. Nick was already sitting at his desk and he smiled widely at her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bringing me coffee?&quot; He asked as she handed him one of the cups. &quot;People are going to start thinking you like me,&quot; he teased and added a wink.<br>
<br>
&quot;Funny,&quot; she said sarcastically, but was also smiling as she sat down. Nick noticed that she seemed happier than usual.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know that look,&quot; he said, causing her to arch an eyebrow at him. &quot;That's the 'I've met a guy' look.&quot; Her smile grew, but she said nothing. &quot;So are you going to tell me about him?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Nope,&quot; she answered. He pretended to be crestfallen at the comment.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ouch, that really hurts Kate.&quot; He clutched his hand at his heart. She rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why?&quot; She asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, primarily because I have no social life right now and I have to live vicariously through others,&quot; he said jokingly. She grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;There's always Carl,&quot; she retorted. His face contorted with disgust and Kate started laughing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Benson! O'Malley! My office now!&quot; Captain Page's bellowing could be heard throughout the unit. Kate and Nick started walking over to his office.<br>
<br>
&quot;So you're really not going to tell me?&quot; Nick asked, a slight tinge of hurt on his words. She shook her head.<br>
<br>
&quot;Not a chance. Any time I tell you about a guy I like it falls through, it's like you're a jinx,&quot; she explained. He cocked his head.<br>
<br>
&quot;Maybe they're just jealous,&quot; he suggested in a kidding manner. She smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't tell them about you,&quot; she responded. He stared at her for a second and smiled. They reached the office, only to find Jonathan already there with what looked like presentation material. Although presentations were usually held in the main lobby, special cases were brought to their attention in Page's office. 'It doesn't matter, I'm not going to let it ruin my day,' Kate thought. They sat down, still holding their 'to go' cups of coffee. Nick leaned over toward Kate while Jonathan was finishing putting his things together.<br>
<br>
&quot;Think if I forge a note from my mom that I can be excused?&quot; He quipped to her in a low volume. She grinned and took a sip of her coffee.<br>
<br>
&quot;Save your smart ass remarks for your own time O'Malley,&quot; Page said gruffly. &quot;We've got a serious situation here today.&quot; Nick smiled, completely unrepentant. &quot;Jonathan.&quot; The young man excitedly started the slide projector.<br>
<br>
&quot;La-dy,&quot; Jonathan strung out his first word, &quot;and gentlemen. May I present.&quot; The first slide came on the screen. &quot;The leprechaun.&quot; Kate arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
&quot;You've got to be kidding me,&quot; she commented as she looked at a cartoon drawing of a leprechaun.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let me finish,&quot; Jonathan said, giving her as stern of a look as he could. Nick chuckled. &quot;As you can see, the common misconception about leprechauns is that they're tiny, or 'little people,'&quot; he used his fingers to make quotation marks during the last part of his sentence. He smiled and looked proud of himself for the research he had done. &quot;This, however, is untrue. They actually look just like humans.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So how are we supposed to find it?&quot; Kate asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;And what kind of ammo do we use?&quot; Nick chimed in. Jonathan's face dropped into an almost panicked expression.<br>
<br>
&quot;No, no, no,&quot; he shook his arms in front of him. &quot;You can't kill it. And I mean that literally. Even if it wasn't way more valuable to us alive, it can't be killed. Stunned or knocked out? Absolutely. But not killed.&quot; Nick smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;We'll see,&quot; he said smugly. Kate hit him on the arm.<br>
<br>
&quot;So why is it dangerous?&quot; She asked. Jonathan pointed a finger at her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Excellent question!&quot; He smiled and Nick rolled his eyes. &quot;The leprechauns are tied into almost every facet of link activity.&quot; Kate grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;So, like Carl?&quot; She asked, although it came out as more of a statement.<br>
<br>
&quot;Uh, well, no. More in control than Carl,&quot; Jonathan answered. Nick's face beamed.<br>
<br>
&quot;So, they're the mob of the link world,&quot; he sniggered. Jonathan looked uneasy.<br>
<br>
&quot;Exactly,&quot; Page confirmed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let me get this straight,&quot; Kate started. &quot;You want us to find a leprechaun, that looks exactly like a human, because you suspect link mob activity?&quot; The disbelief was evident in her voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;If it helps, they usually wear green,&quot; Page said in a not quite consoling voice. She stared at him in astonishment.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's almost St. Patrick's Day! Most of the city is wearing green!&quot; She exclaimed as she rose from her seat. Nick got a smirky yet thoughtful look on his face.<br>
<br>
&quot;She's got a point sir,&quot; he said. Page nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't worry, we've got some good leads,&quot; he paused and shrugged. He turned to Kate. &quot;And, if those don't pan out, I'm sure O'Malley will have fun using links as target practice until they tell us what we want to know.&quot; Nick's face lit up.<br>
<br>
&quot;Really?&quot; He asked, his voice full of glee. Page rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;We're on the clock here people,&quot; he responded, ignoring Nick. &quot;St. Patrick's Day marks the high point of power for leprechauns, and now that they've established strong ties into the link community,&quot; he got a far away look in his eyes, &quot;There's no telling the havoc they could wreak if we don't stop them.&quot;<br>
