<br>
&quot;So you're really not going to tell me?&quot; Nick asked. He glanced over at Kate, but quickly turned his attention back to the road. Carl peeked his head between the two from the back seat. He looked at Kate with a smile.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tell him what?&quot; He asked. Kate shook her head and said nothing.<br>
<br>
&quot;She has a new guy, but she won't tell me anything about him,&quot; Nick explained with a smile.<br>
<br>
&quot;Jealous?&quot; Carl sneered back at him. Nick rolled his eyes and punched his hand back at him. The car swerved and Kate grabbed the wheel. Nick just grinned and took over driving again.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're sure this is where we can find your contact?&quot; Kate asked Carl suspiciously. The old warehouse district was home to plenty of links, but they tended not to set up permanent residence there. Nick pulled the car over and parked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah, yeah, I'm sure,&quot; Carl said non-chalantly as he opened the back door. Nick and Kate both glared at him, indicating that he should stay in the car. &quot;No way, you guys are the outsiders here. I,&quot; he motioned to himself, &quot;on the other hand, am with my peeps.&quot; Nick and Kate looked at each other in a glib and defeated manner.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fine,&quot; Nick agreed and slapped Carl on the back of the head. &quot;Don't break anything.&quot;<br>
<br>
The warehouse was old and should have been condemned was Kate's first thought; but then, that's probably why the links liked the area, not a lot of human competition except for storage people. They opened a door to a small room inside the warehouse, only to be met by glowing green eyes and a foul odor. Kate cringed and quickly covered her mouth and nose with her hand. Nick did the same.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, what? My aroma offending your delicate human senses?&quot; The link and Carl both laughed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey Morty,&quot; Carl greeted his friend officially. &quot;I hear you got a piece of that job over on Michigan last week,&quot; he said, obviously impressed. Morty nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;Didn't get to join 'em in taking out the place, but I planned it out. Thirty percent,&quot; he replied, proud of himself. Kate cleared her throat and Nick shot Carl a look when he turned around to look at them. He rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fine. If you don't want to give me time to catch up with an old friend,&quot; Carl said.<br>
<br>
&quot;We don't,&quot; Nick said immediately. Carl glared at him, but turned back to Morty.<br>
<br>
&quot;We need some help finding a leprechaun,&quot; he said in a grumbling manner. Morty started laughing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah right,&quot; he finally said. He glanced at the expressions on the detectives' faces. &quot;You're serious,&quot; he observed. &quot;Crap. If I tell you anything, I'll be dead before tomorrow.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That's a chance I'm willing to take,&quot; Kate said. Nick turned his head and smiled broadly at her.<br>
<br>
&quot;That's a chance I'm willing to inflict,&quot; Nick added in a happy voice, raising his gun to aim at the link. Morty's arms, all six of them, flailed wildly in the air.<br>
<br>
&quot;Okay, okay,&quot; he said. &quot;But it didn't come from me.&quot; Nick and Kate nodded. Morty directed them to a restaurant/pub in the middle of the restaurant district called Eogan's. The place looked nice from the outside, but it was still early in the day, and the door was locked. Nick got out his gun, but Kate put her hand on his arm.<br>
<br>
&quot;Warrant?&quot; She asked, trying to remind him that he was still a police officer. He smiled and looked around to make sure no one was watching, and then he shot the lock. He opened the door and he turned to Kate again.<br>
<br>
&quot;That's the nice thing about links, they don't have rights,&quot; he quipped. She shook her head, but followed him in. It was a nice establishment, probably pretty pricey if they were there to actually eat.<br>
<br>
&quot;And if they're not links?&quot; She asked as she looked around the place. Nick shrugged.<br>
<br>
&quot;Whoops?&quot; He offered with a smug smile. She shook her head and smiled. They began to look around, but no one was there.<br>
<br>
&quot;Maybe we should come back later, put a car outside to let us know when someone actually shows up,&quot; Kate said. All of the paperwork in the offices seemed to be business related, and there were no signs, other than the fact that it was an Irish named establishment, to indicate that there was any kind of leprechaun-link activity. Nick nodded in agreement.<br>
<br>
&quot;You ever get the feeling like you're on a wild goose chase?&quot; He asked as they made their way back to the main door. She sighed.<br>
<br>
&quot;All the time.&quot;<br>
<br>
They walked out to the car and Kate thought she heard someone calling her name. Both turned to face the good-looking man coming toward them. Kate smiled and Nick frowned. The man quickly pulled Kate into a hug and gave her a small kiss. Nick raised an eyebrow, but quickly put on his best 'this doesn't bother me' face.<br>
<br>
&quot;Do I get an introduction?&quot; He asked. Kate and the man turned to face him, both with smiles on their faces.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nick, this is Trevor, Trevor, Nick,&quot; she introduced the two men. They shook hands.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nice to finally meet you,&quot; Trevor said. Nick smiled and made a mental note of the light Irish accent.<br>
<br>
&quot;You too.&quot; He looked at Kate. &quot;Kate's been talking about you a lot lately,&quot; he said, biting back a chuckle at his teasing her. She glared at him for a moment, but let it pass. Trevor looked at Kate lovingly, which made Nick feel queasy, but he covered it well.<br>
<br>
&quot;So what were you two doing at Eogan's? It's a little early for lunch,&quot; Trevor commented. Kate and Nick shared a look.<br>
<br>
&quot;Just business,&quot; she answered. Trevor arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
&quot;Really? Will you be arresting my cousin then? Because that would be fantastic,&quot; he said with a smile. Kate looked surprised.<br>
<br>
&quot;Your cousin?&quot; She asked. He shrugged.<br>
<br>
&quot;He owns the place,&quot; he said as if it was nothing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Really?&quot; Nick asked. If he wasn't suspicious of the guy before he met him, he certainly was now.<br>
