<br>
&quot;He isn't,&quot; Kate argued. She was getting sick of this conversation.<br>
<br>
&quot;Isn't what?&quot; Captain Page asked as he strolled toward them. Apparently their voices had been a little louder than they thought.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nick thinks my boyfriend is a leprechaun,&quot; she said in an exasperated voice and rolled her eyes. Nick frowned.<br>
<br>
&quot;When did he get upgraded to boyfriend status?&quot; He asked. She glared at him.<br>
<br>
&quot;When you argued with me the entire ride back to the station,&quot; she answered. Page looked back and forth between the two.<br>
<br>
&quot;That's enough,&quot; he said. Both officers grumbled. He looked at Nick. &quot;What makes you think he's a leprechaun?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;His cousin owns Eogan's, the restaurant where Carl's friend directed us,&quot; Nick said. Page nodded. &quot;And he has a little bit of an Irish accent.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sounds like a valid lead,&quot; he agreed. Nick smirked. &quot;So what's the problem? Why didn't you bring him in?&quot; Kate's mouth dropped open a little to protest.<br>
<br>
&quot;He's my boyfriend!&quot; She said emphatically. &quot;And he's not a leprechaun!&quot; She started to walk toward her desk. &quot;What's the matter with you people?&quot; She mumbled. Carl, who was sitting nearby, overheard her.<br>
<br>
&quot;You want a list?&quot; He laughed, but quickly shut up when she shot him a death glare. He raised his hands in mock surrender. &quot;Staying out of it.&quot; Captain Page came up to O'Malley.<br>
<br>
&quot;How serious is this 'relationship' she's involved in?&quot; He asked. Nick frowned.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know, but I'll find out,&quot; Nick answered. He walked to his desk and smiled across at Kate. &quot;I'm sorry.&quot; She looked up at him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Really?&quot; She asked. His smile grew wider.<br>
<br>
&quot;Absolutely. Just because his cousin is a leprechaun, it doesn't mean that he is,&quot; he smirked. She narrowed her eyes at him and then smiled and shook her head.<br>
<br>
&quot;Have you considered the possibility that Morty was just lying to us?&quot; She asked. Nick nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;Of course,&quot; he said. &quot;But that's because it's in my nature to be suspicious.&quot; Kate sighed.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're just not going to let this go are you?&quot; She asked and he smiled again.<br>
<br>
&quot;You know me surprisingly well,&quot; he answered.<br>
<br>
&quot;What do you want me to do? I'm going out with him tonight.&quot; She sounded frustrated. He seemed to perk up, not at the fact that she was dating him, but at the plan forming in his head.<br>
<br>
&quot;You could wear a wire,&quot; he suggested. She glared at him.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're joking,&quot; she said as she looked at him. He said nothing. &quot;You're not joking. Do you know how uncomfortable those things are? Not to mention if he comes back to my place.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So don't invite him back to your place,&quot; Nick said, a little too cheerfully. Kate buried her head in her hands.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're impossible. You realize that?&quot; It came out as more of a statement.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah, but that's why you love me right?&quot; He smirked.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm not wearing a wire.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What are you gonna do? Just come right out and ask if he's a leprechaun?&quot; Nick laughed. Kate got a sardonic grin on her face and stood up.<br>
<br>
&quot;That's exactly what I'm going to do,&quot; she said. He looked at her, his smile started to fall when he realized she was serious. She started to leave the building.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh crap,&quot; he mumbled and got up to follow her.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey sweetheart,&quot; Trevor greeted her when he saw her come into the restaurant. He gave her a kiss and then looked briefly at Nick. &quot;Couldn't stay away from me huh?&quot; He teased. Kate smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Actually, I had something to ask you,&quot; she said. Nick leaned over to speak in her ear.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't do this,&quot; he warned in a low voice, but still smiling as to not tip off Trevor. Kate kept the smile on her face.<br>
<br>
&quot;What is it?&quot; Trevor asked. &quot;Oh, did you want some lunch? You can join me at my table.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright,&quot; Kate agreed. On the way to the table, Nick grabbed her arm loosely.<br>
<br>
&quot;I mean it, you're going to get us killed,&quot; he said, still trying to keep his voice upbeat. She tilted her head to speak to him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh what? But it was perfectly okay just to have me be the one who got killed?&quot; She asked. Nick pretended to think about it and then grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well.&quot; he said. She hit him on the arm and he laughed. Trevor pulled a chair out for Kate and then sat next to her. Nick sat across from them. Trevor took hold of Kate's hand and flashed her a brilliant smile that made his eyes gleam.<br>
<br>
&quot;So what did you want to ask me love?&quot; He asked. She smirked at Nick and then turned her attention back to Trevor.<br>
<br>
&quot;My idiot partner,&quot; she motioned to Nick with her head, &quot;thinks that you're a leprechaun.&quot; Trevor eyed Nick suspiciously.<br>
<br>
&quot;Does he now?&quot;<br>
<br>
