<br>
&quot;Yeah,&quot; he confirmed. Trevor narrowed his eyes at him. Nick smirked. He turned to Kate. &quot;Notice that he hasn't denied it.&quot; She crossed her arms and gave him a 'you're unbelievable' look.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why would I deny it?&quot; Trevor asked in an Irish lilt. Kate turned in his direction, completely surprised.<br>
<br>
&quot;What?!&quot; Kate asked loudly. Trevor shrugged and leaned back in his chair.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why would I bother to confirm or deny such a ridiculous accusation?&quot; Trevor clarified. Kate let out a breath and grinned. She smugly glared at Nick, who in return smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Then you won't mind this,&quot; Nick said and got out a vial containing a purple liquid. Kate looked questioningly at him. Nick poured a little bit of the liquid onto Trevor's hand and Trevor jumped up and screamed in pain as the liquid burned through his skin. Kate quickly reached for a napkin and tried to dab off the wound.<br>
<br>
&quot;What did you do?&quot; She asked Nick accusingly, who looked completely unrepentant. His smile had only grown.<br>
<br>
&quot;Captain Page thought it would be better if we didn't let you in on that little detail,&quot; he responded and motioned to Trevor with his head. &quot;Take a look at your perfect boyfriend now.&quot; Kate stared wide-eyed at Trevor, who had shrunk down to no more than half a foot tall and now had pointy ears.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh my God,&quot; she said under her breath. Nick reached over and picked him up, stealthily putting him in a silver briefcase he had brought with them for that precise purpose. A waiter hurried over to the table.<br>
<br>
&quot;Is anything wrong here?&quot; He asked. Nick smiled and shook his head.<br>
<br>
&quot;I think our friend had a reaction to something in the food, so he went to use the restroom,&quot; Nick smoothly lied. &quot;Unfortunately, we've just been called back to work. If he comes back, tell him lunch was on me,&quot; he said as he placed a fifty dollar bill on the table. The waiter nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;No problem sir,&quot; the waiter replied. He could ignore the scream he just heard knowing that it meant a sizeable tip for him. Nick and Kate walked out to the car. Kate sat with her arms crossed the entire ride back to the station.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aw, don't be mad,&quot; Nick said.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're enjoying this aren't you?&quot; She asked pointedly. He smiled and tilted his head.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes,&quot; he admitted. &quot;But not as much as if I had just been able to kill him.&quot; Kate shook her head in frustration and stared out the window.<br>
<br>
&quot;He's a good guy Nick,&quot; she finally said. He grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;He's a link Kate,&quot; he replied.<br>
<br>
&quot;Maybe it doesn't matter.&quot; Her luck with guys had been very poor lately. It was almost as if someone had put the word out not to go near her. Then, she met Trevor, and she thought her luck was turning around. She knew she shouldn't blame Nick, it wasn't his fault that Trevor was a link, but he didn't have to be so smug about it. Nick, on the other hand, couldn't believe the words that had just come out of her mouth.<br>
<br>
&quot;What?!&quot; He practically yelled in disbelief. &quot;How can you say it doesn't matter?&quot; He pulled the car over and they stepped out, walking into the drycleaners front. &quot;Kate, you're not thinking rationally.&quot; She refused to look at him.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm not thinking rationally? Trevor is the first guy I've met in a long time that has actually liked me and treated me decently. He's the first guy who has bothered to send me flowers and.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;God, you didn't sleep with him did you?&quot; Nick interrupted. &quot;Please tell me you didn't sleep with him.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not yet, but I would have,&quot; she responded. He grimaced and made a face.<br>
<br>
&quot;Geez Kate, if you were that desperate, I would have.&quot; he stopped talking when he received a harsh glare from her eyes. He shrugged it off and smiled. &quot;Of course, I would have anyway.&quot; Kate's mouth dropped open to make a comment but quickly closed in confusion.<br>
<br>
&quot;What?&quot;<br>
<br>
