<br>
&quot;So, you're saying that you don't know anything about what's going down on St. Patrick's Day?&quot; Captain Page asked Trevor. He had been returned to his human size, but was in restraints.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lots of people getting drunk and wearing green,&quot; Trevor answered with a smirk.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why do I think he knows more than that?&quot; Nick asked. Trevor smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're looking a little green yourself there boy-o.&quot; Nick didn't fail to catch Trevor's meaning, as green was the color associated with jealousy. He nodded once and smiled back.<br>
<br>
&quot;You know the nice thing about that problem?&quot; Nick asked and Trevor raised an eyebrow. Nick raised his gun and aimed it at Trevor's head. &quot;It's easily solvable.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;O'Malley!&quot; Page called him to him, but he just looked at him briefly through the corner of his eye. Nick lowered his weapon.<br>
<br>
&quot;You never let me have any fun,&quot; Nick grumbled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Information first, then you can kill him,&quot; Page retorted. A broad smile came over Nick's mouth. He nodded and smirked at Trevor.<br>
<br>
&quot;This is shaping up to be my lucky day,&quot; he quipped. Trevor rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't suppose I get to see Kate any time soon?&quot; He asked. Page stared blankly at him in disbelief and Nick scowled.<br>
<br>
&quot;No,&quot; they both answered. Page turned to O'Malley.<br>
<br>
&quot;Maybe I should let you handle the interrogation alone for a while,&quot; he said. Trevor winced when he saw the almost evil look spread across Nick's face.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good idea sir,&quot; Nick responded in a cheery tone. He watched Captain Page leave the room and shut the door behind him, and then he turned around to face Trevor. &quot;So, there's the easy way or the hard way.&quot; Trevor raised an eyebrow skeptically.<br>
<br>
&quot;The easy way is?&quot; He asked. Nick smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;You tell me what I want to know and then I kill you,&quot; he said in a happy voice. Trevor frowned.<br>
<br>
&quot;Dare I ask what the hard way is?&quot; He watched Nick shrug.<br>
<br>
&quot;The hard way is that I just kill you and don't get the information,&quot; Nick retorted. Trevor furrowed his brow.<br>
<br>
&quot;How is either of those easy for me?&quot; He asked. Nick chuckled.<br>
<br>
&quot;I didn't say for you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't think Kate will forgive you if you kill her boyfriend,&quot; Trevor grinned. Nick shrugged again and aimed his gun.<br>
<br>
&quot;She has before,&quot; Nick said with a straight face. Trevor went pale.<br>
<br>
&quot;How about a different deal, one where I don't end up dead at the end?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know, that doesn't sound like much fun.&quot; Nick lowered his gun, but still kept it ready to fire.<br>
<br>
&quot;I tell you what you want to know and you let me see Kate,&quot; Trevor said.<br>
<br>
&quot;No deal.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I am still her boyfriend you know.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Somehow I doubt that,&quot; Nick said. &quot;Kate's really big on the whole honesty thing and you, well, you're a leprechaun. And, maybe it's just me, but she seemed kind of surprised by that.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;She was angrier with you about that if I recall correctly,&quot; Trevor grinned. Nick cocked his head to the side and smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah, but she knows me,&quot; he replied.<br>
<br>
Trevor finally gave in and told Nick what they needed to know, he figured they couldn't stop it now anyway, but only on the condition that he got to see Kate. Nick only agreed to the deal after Page forced him to. There was a light rap on the door and then Kate entered. He raised his eyebrow at her and she grinned. Kate patted Nick on the shoulder.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's okay,&quot; she said. He nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;You want me to stay?&quot; He asked. She shook her head.<br>
<br>
&quot;I got it,&quot; she said and he opened the door. &quot;But stay nearby just in case,&quot; she threw over her shoulder. She sat down across from Trevor. &quot;So.&quot; He grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;I wanted to tell you Kate,&quot; he said. His voice sounded honest, but then, even Carl could sound honest when he wanted to.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why didn't you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, believe it or not, but there aren't that many attractive women who actually believe that leprechauns even exist.&quot; He gave a self-deprecating laugh. &quot;I thought you'd try to have me committed.&quot; Kate laughed.<br>
<br>
&quot;I guess that's true,&quot; she agreed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where does this leave us then?&quot; He asked. She sighed.<br>
<br>
&quot;I like you Trevor, but.&quot; She shook her head. He nodded in understanding and smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Promise me you'll call if things don't work out with him?&quot; He asked. She opened her mouth to speak, but quickly shut it and smiled instead. Two officers took him away to lock-up and Kate sat back down at her desk. Nick looked over at her, a little concerned.<br>
<br>
&quot;You okay?&quot; He asked. She smiled and nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah,&quot; she answered. He looked at her questioningly, taking in the expression on her face.<br>
<br>
&quot;If I didn't know you any better, I'd say you have another guy waiting for you,&quot; he said. Her smile grew wider and his mouth dropped open. &quot;So you're gonna tell me who he is right?&quot; He smiled and she shook her head.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nope.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ka-te!&quot; He drew out her name in exasperation.<br>
<br>
&quot;No,&quot; she smiled smugly.<br>
<br>
&quot;You have to tell me. I think we've all seen what happens when you don't tell me,&quot; Nick said in a bemused voice. She laughed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, Trevor said if it doesn't work out with him that I should give him a call,&quot; Kate said. Nick's smile fell a little and Kate kept laughing.<br>
<br>
&quot;That's not funny.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It is.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It's not,&quot; he insisted. She finally stopped laughing and smiled at him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Pizza?&quot; She asked, getting up from her chair. He followed her lead and got up from his chair as well.<br>
<br>
&quot;Only if you tell me who the guy is,&quot; he said in a bribing tone. She rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;We'll see.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
